<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kayleigh</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ok. I read Bryll's post on the item evaluation as I gather many people have. And it's wonderful, but unfortunately it's six months out of date and doesn't have anything from Velious on it.<P>It'd be really great if someone updated the list, maybe put together a spreadsheet so new things could be easily added and you could adjust the weightings to your own preference.<P>So I did.  I have a spreadsheet of the original list Bryll did, and I added a few Velious items that I was aware of. (No I didn't do a comprehensive update but you can easily add in your own items and see the score.)<P>Is there a way I can post this file for everyone?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aenae</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">To post your file, try creating a file repository on Geocities.com or some equivalent, and then just link to it from here.<P>This is what I use for my signature pictues (ezboard) and other misc posts.<P>- Aenae Webspinner<BR>- Priestess of Luclin</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aenae</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">If you want, email me the file and I'll host it for you.<P>- Aenae Webspinner<BR>- Aenae_Luclin@Yahoo.com</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kayleigh</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Let's try this and see if it works. According to my friend it should.<BR> <A HREF="http://www.idrive.com/wingblaze/files/Shared/cleric+items.xls" TARGET=_blank>http://www.idrive.com/wingblaze/files/Shared/cleric+items.xls</A> <P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Suesc</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Bumpity bumpity bump<P><BR>Leo<BR>The Quicker Vicar</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kayleigh</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Also Havon has posted this sheet for easier viewing (I heard some people had problems with the other link)<BR> <A HREF="http://havan_ironoak.tripod.com/clericitems.xls" TARGET=_blank>http://havan_ironoak.tripod.com/clericitems.xls</A> </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Drusk</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">On my computer, the first file is not accesible and the second tells me that Excel can't open it.  Something about it being read-only or something.<P>------------------<BR>Drusk Urdrom<BR>Level 25 Cleric<BR>Saryrn Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dunnar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Add Gauntlets of the Black on the hands page....</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kayleigh</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">On my personal copy I already did. And you can do the same on yours  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/wink.gif"><P>That's why the intitial post said:<P>"(No I didn't do a comprehensive update but you can easily add in your own items and see the score.)"<P> <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/wink.gif"><P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kayleigh</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aw what happened to my smiley faces?<P><pouts><P>Sorry that sounds kinda mean without the smileys.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">naxy</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I wondered a bit about having strenght add a positive score in this equipment list without taking into account the weight of the item. <P>For example: Platinum Armbands (STR3/WIS3/WEIGHT0.4) score 36 vs. Vambraces of the Fervent (AC11/DEX5/FIRERES5/WEIGHT4.9) score 46.<P>If you take into account the weight as well, say -3 score per weight unit (STR adds 3 per unit) then the Platinum Armbands score 35 and Vambraces of the Fervent score 32. <P>Now, I am not saying that I know what the correct scoring for weight should be, but it seems as STR is very important to some of us, scoring for STR bonus without taking into account weight is going to give slightly off results.<P>I am currently modifying my version of the spreadsheet to add the weight to every item, I cannot decide what the score for weight should be though.<P>How would you score the weight, considering that STR is a plus 3 per unit?<P>Naxy<P>------------------<BR>Naxy Dent Cleric of Karana on Bristlebane</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kayleigh</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I had some of the same thoughts. As a high elf, all this heavy armor can be of concern to me.<P>But the original post didn't include weight, and I didn't want to go do the research for it.<P>But your point is well taken - if you consider that the only real reason for strength is to carry things (given that we will never do much melee damage unless you're Lerwin and get 5 procs of dawnfire in a fight) then some kind of weighting to take into account strength given vs item weight might be appropriate.<P>You can also make arguments for the usefulness of various effects and different scoring there. In the end the sheet is really a guideline, and not an absolute.  If your wisdom is maxed, other things become more important. As you get higher level, resistances become more important.<P>For me, it sometimes helps me keep my eye on the ball as far as where I want my equipment to go.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">naxy</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Well I have started the research, so far I have covered Vambracers/Arm. he he he. It will take a while. Not like I have nothing else to do.  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>------------------<BR>Naxy Dent Cleric of Karana on Bristlebane</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Eidolon Hammerstroke</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Weight of the item has always been a concern for me since I haven't taken the time to get many weight reducing packs (they're on my list, though).<P>I added the <A HREF="http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/item.html?item=4061" TARGET=_blank>Lodizal Shell Shield</A> and using +20 for the resists gives the shield a 237 rating. Using +10 gives it a 232 rating. <p>[This message has been edited by Eidolon Hammerstroke (edited 03-01-2001).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Icaro</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Can some of you uber guys post an upgraded version of the original post including Kunark and Velious items? It would save me and lots of friends I know are aware of this list a lot of research time.<P>I know, prolly noone will do but thanks in advance anyway.<P>Icaro.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dunnar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Bumpitty bump bump<P>Anyone have an updated version of this?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Mahtan Honorshield</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Check this thread:  <A HREF="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/Forum3/HTML/002153.html" TARGET=_blank>http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/Forum3/HTML/002153.html</A> .</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">sertain</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Just thought I might bump this in case some new folks had never seen the last link in it.  It is a great thing for an aspiring cleric.  I know I loved it when I played more.<P>Sertain</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
